1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
What if I told you ecosystems are more like webs than chains?

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:08,000
Food chains simplify relationships into a linear path.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:10,000
But nature is much messier.

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,800
Picture this: a spider spins a web.

5
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:16,400
Every strand connects to multiple insects, not just one.

6
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:20,400
In a food web, one animal can play multiple roles.

7
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:24,800
A rabbit isn’t just food; it can also be a pollinator.

8
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:28,000
Understanding food webs helps us grasp ecosystem health.

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,800
A stronger web means a healthier planet.

10
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,200
Want to dive deeper into ecology?

11
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,600
Like and follow for more insights!
